Package org.neo4j.test.extension.actors

Interface Actor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ActorImpl
    public interface Actor
    An independent test actor that runs in its own thread.

    Tasks can be submitted to this thread and be executed in order, and its state can be inspected.

    Instances of this interface are acquired by having them injected into instance fields of test classes. This requires that the test class are running with the ActorsExtension.

      • untilWaiting

        void untilWaiting()
           throws InterruptedException
        Wait for the actor thread to enter a waiting state.

        A waiting state means that the actor thread state is one of Thread.State.WAITING or Thread.State.TIMED_WAITING.

        If there are no tasks running or queued, then an IllegalStateException will be thrown to prevent the actor and the calling thread from live-locking.

        If the actor thread has terminated (which only happens after the test method has returned) then an AssertionError is thrown.

        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if the calling thread is interrupted while waiting for the actor to enter a waiting state.

      • untilWaitingIn

        void untilWaitingIn​(Executable constructorOrMethod)
             throws InterruptedException
        Waits for the actor thread to enter a waiting state inside the given method or constructor.

        Here is an example of how this can be used: 

        
 @ActorsExtension
 class ExampleTest
 {
    @Inject
    Actor actor;

    @Test
    void example() throws Exception
    {
        actor.submit( new Sleeper()::sleep );
        actor.untilWaitingIn( Sleeper.class.getMethod( "sleep" ) );
        actor.interrupt();
    }

    class Sleeper
    {
        public void sleep()
        {
            try
            {
                Thread.sleep( 1_000 );
            }
            catch ( InterruptedException ignore )
            {
            }
        }
    }
 }
        Parameters:
        constructorOrMethod - The Method or Constructor that the actor should be waiting in.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - If the calling thread is interrupted while waiting for the actor thread to reach the intended state.

      • untilWaitingIn

        void untilWaitingIn​(String methodName)
             throws InterruptedException
        Waits for the actor thread to enter a waiting state inside any method with the given name.

        This is similar to untilWaitingIn(Executable), but can also be used for when the target class cannot be referenced from the test code. For instance, if the class is anonymous, or not public.

        Parameters:
        methodName - The name of the method wherein the actor should be waiting.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - If the calling thread is interrupted while waiting for the actor thread to reach the intended state.

      • untilThreadState

        void untilThreadState​(Thread.State... states)
        Waits for the actor thread to enter any of the given states.

        Note that unlike untilWaiting(), this method will not throw any exception if the actor has no submitted tasks, or is terminated. This means that it is possible to live-lock with the actor thread.

        Parameters:
        states - The set of states to wait for.

      • interrupt

        void interrupt()
        Interrupt the actor thread.
